Text.string: Oi! Vault Hunter. Need somethin' from ya.
Slag me, I'm tired. Proper knackered.
Solid kill, Vault Hunter! That guy was a real wank-muffin. Now grab the power core!
Look, I'm sorry, but I'm the only thing standing between these civilians and a Maliwan armada. This coffee is gonna save lives. Starting with mine.
Oh, hey. What can I do to, like... help you? Or whatever?
Ooooh, can't do it. Power core just blew out, and I can't do the coffee thing without the power thing.
Why does every damn thing always need a damn power core?
Why are power cores always so damn unreliable?
Ah, yes. The ubiquitous power core problem. Naturally.
Power cores. It's always the damn power cores, isn't it?
Lemme get some Arcturian superblack, Mr. Bot.
I'll have some Arcturian superblack, if you would.
I need some Arcturian superblack.
Ey, boyo. Need a cup of Arcturian superblack.
Oh, man, no can do. We're, like, an eco-friendly shop, y'know? So, you'll have to supply your own to-go cup.
Guess I gotta take matters into my own hands! Let's do this, Vaulter!
Now pick up the mug!
I'd love a cup of coffee right now.
Honestly, that caffeinated sewer juice Maliwan calls coffee is practically a war crime on its own. I just want that commander's mug.
Oh, man, we're soooo bloody close! I can almost taste that Arcturian superblack already. Hurry back to the shop! Come on!
Lorelei, I hear you and I super understand. Please just chill.
Lorelei, have you ever considered switching to chai?
I can feel the intensity of your need from here.
I hear ya. What I wouldn't do for a pint right now.
Hey, we've all got our vices.
Damn it! Can't you leave me one good thing, Maliwan? Just one cup of goddamn coffee?!
Whoa, guys, please! Just form a line and I'll get to your orders. You know. Eventually.
Those dudes were the literal worst.
Barista Bot. Just shut up and get us the coffee.
Sure, sure. Don't bust an aneurysm or whatever. Just show me that to-go cup and I'll fill it up for you.
Cool, locally sourced, righteous. Now hold on.
I'm craving a perfectly steeped Arcturian superblack. That sound when it hits the cup. The sweet heat of that first sip. If you've never had it... you just don't understand.
What... is... taking so long?!
Ughhh. Would you please hurry up?
I do not have all day.
No, no. Take your time. I don't have anywhere else to be.
Whatever, man. You can't rush perfection.
Yes! YES! Finally! Bring that coffee here.
You are my favorite person. This was SO necessary.
Ah, bollocks! Maliwan's here! Come on, then! Let's show 'em what a little caffeine does for our morale!
We really can't thank you enough, Vault Hunter. I know this seems like a small thing, but... even this little taste of the world we lost... it keeps us going, y'know? At least till tomorrow morning.
Don't forget to pick up the power core!
You'll need that power core to get Rise and Grind running again.
Go on, grab the power core.
Power core! Get it.
Shop's powered up! Can we get that coffee now, Barista Bot?
Go on, ring the bell.
Ring the bell and get a barista bot out here!
Just ring the bell, Vault Hunter.
Ding-a-ling! Ring the bell. Need the coffee.
Man, what I wouldn't do for some coffee.
Come on, come on, come on! What is taking so long?!
Annnd you're welcome. Have a lovely day. Or don't, your call.
Well done, Vault Hunter! Now come on over for a well-earned reward.

Whaddya say we start civilizing this war-torn city again? Let's start with the most precious commodity of all: coffee. I'm feelin' right ragged, and when a commander makes mistakes, people die. And I'm sure my troops could use a pick-me-up as well. Head to the Rise and Grind coffee shop to get started.
'Ey, Atlas boys! Rise and Grind's back in business and the coffee's on me!
Yeah. Rise and Grind's deserted, but there should be a barista bot you can call up. They're, uh... really annoying, but the coffee's worth it.

Of COURSE! But it's okay. It's ooookay. Right, there's a Maliwan Heavy nearby, calls himself “Core Daddy” like a real asshole. Bloke's got a power core built right into his suit. That'll get us up and running!
Y'know, it's funny—I used to say things like, “I'll kill anyone who talks to me before I've had my coffee.” But now I literally might!||I dunno, that's—that's just funny to me.
There you go. Now head back to the shop, and GET ME SOME DAMN COFFEE ALREADY!
Now plug in that power core!
Use the power core and get the shop running again!
Just shove that power core in there, Vault Hunter.
Power core goes in, coffee comes out.
Take out some of the rank and file to draw out the commander. That mug is mine.
Well, bollocks. Wait, wait, I know! There's a Maliwan commander who's always got a travel mug on him. See if you can track him down.
Maliwan's attacking the shop!
Maliwan dropped in for a fight!
Maliwan is assaulting the shop!
Maliwan's lookin' for a bloody nose!
Just let the bot do his work! It'll be so, so worth it.
Woo-hoo-hoo-hoo, YEAH!
We did it! Hell yes!
Oh, hell yeah!
For real? Thanks, Lorelei!
I've gotta get this coffee to the commander! Outta my way, Vaulter!
Looks like the coffee break's over, boys! Let's get 'em!
So, you've killed my coffee runner. No big loss. But you stole my mug and I WILL have it back! I am the one and only Coffee Commander!
I know you have the mug, Vaulter! I'm ordering my troops to re-acquire it at all costs! We will NOT let it remain in enemy hands!
Give up the mug, Vaulter! I'll never stop pursuing it!
I just loved that mug... so much...
Wait, what does it say? “World's Greatest Commander”? That is so totally mine! I'M the Coffee Commander now!
Cool, cool cool. Very cool. Now hit the bell. That should reboot the shop or whatever. And my facial flair.
Voilà. Or whatever.
Screw you, Vaulter! I was just tryin' ta get my coffee on!
I was on break, dammit! Now I gotta kill this Vaulter?!
